              <% include ../_partials/content/_bluenav-general.ejs %>

                <article class="blade wrapper content">
                    <!-- article -->

                    <div>
                      <h1>Port Forwarding :: Vodafone EasyBox</h1>
                      <p> <i>This is the 2nd step of the Port Forwarding, click <a href="/Fernzugriff/Der_DDNS_Dienst/">here</a> to get to the beginning of the manual.</i></p>
                        <br>
                        <amp-youtube data-videoid="CF8W5N4Q8Ws" layout="responsive" width="480" height="270" class="shadow"></amp-youtube>
                        <br>
                        <h3>Step 1</h3>
                        <p>To access the user interface of your router open the following address with your internet browser <a href="http://192.168.2.1">192.168.2.1</a>. The <strong>default login</strong> is username = root or admin and password = 123456. Navigate to the <strong>Port Mapping</strong> in the <em>Data</em> tab and click on the <strong>Edit</strong> symbol under Configure.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <amp-img
                          on="tap:Easybox_01en"
                          role="button"
                          tabindex="0"
                          src="/images/Internet_Access/Easybox_01en.jpg" width="680" height="257" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                      </amp-img>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <h3>Step 2</h3>
                        <p>Type your camera´s IP address into the field <em>LAN IP</em>. Set both the <strong>LAN</strong> and <strong>Public Port</strong> to the port of your camera. For your first camera both ports are "8081", for your second camera "8082" etc. Click the <strong>Enter</strong>-Symbol under Configure to save the service.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <amp-img
                          on="tap:Easybox_02en"
                          role="button"
                          tabindex="0"
                          src="/images/Internet_Access/Easybox_02en.jpg" width="680" height="280" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                      </amp-img>
                      <p>The service is now active.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <amp-img
                          on="tap:Easybox_03en"
                          role="button"
                          tabindex="0"
                          src="/images/Internet_Access/Easybox_03en.jpg" width="680" height="275" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                      </amp-img>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <h3>Step 3</h3>
                        <p>To be able to access the Flash-Video as well, there has to be set a second Port Forwarding. Therefore just follow the manual of this step, with the only difference to to set the Flash-Port instead. So for your first camera all ports are set to 1935, for your second camera it´s 1936, etc.</p>
                        <p>Now all Port Forwarings for your camera are set in the router. You can now continue with the next step, therefore follow this Link:</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                      <div class="margin">
                        <h3>Step III : The Camera´s DDNS-Address and the Remote-Access</h3>
                          <br>
                          <a href="/Internet_Access/Mobile_Access/"><button type="button" class="btn">Step III</button></a>
                      </div>
